<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 24 at 4:54PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...PATCHY DENSE FOG THIS EVENING
Patchy dense fog has developed across portions of the mid Hudson
Valley, eastern Catskills, southern Berkshires and northwest
Connecticut and will continue into tonight. Visibilities will
lower to one half mile or less at times.
Motorists may encounter fluctuating visibilities over short
distances. If driving through dense fog, slow down, use low beam
headlights, and leave plenty of distance between your vehicle and
others.</description>
